# ALM SM - Bestinver Securities - 11 May 2026
HOLD maintained (Bestinver's text flags upside to BUY). 1Q26 EBITDA beat on cost control; guidance reaffirmed.

## What changed
1Q26 reported vs. Bestinver Securities vs. consensus (€m):

| Metric | Reported (YoY) | Bestinver 1Q26E | Diff. | Consensus 1Q26E | Diff. |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| Net sales | 291 (+2%) | 293 | -1% | 293 | -1% |
| EBITDA | 68 (-5%) | 66 | +2% | 67 | +1% |
| EBIT | 30 (-12%) | 29 | +5% | 29 | +2% |
| Net Profit | 15 (-29%) | 18 | -14% | 19 | -20% |
| EBITDA margin | 23.2% (-172bps) | 22.7% | — | 22.7% | — |

EBITDA beat both Bestinver's and consensus's estimates; net profit missed both (p.7-8).

## Why it changed, and why now
The YoY sales comparison is distorted by a €12m one-off in 1Q25 (Algidol divestment/Sekisan out-licensing); excluding that, sales grew +7% (p.7). Growth was driven by Ebglyss (2x YoY to €42m), Ilumetri (+12%), Wynzora (+21%) and Klisyri (+7%) (p.7). Gross margin eroded 274bps YoY (129bps like-for-like) on higher Ilumetri royalty tiers, but the EBITDA beat came from R&D and SG&A costs moderating annually — margin was 159bps better than 1Q26 margin ex one-offs (p.7). Net debt swung to €26.2m (from €2m net cash) on higher capex and seasonal working capital (p.7).

Almirall reaffirmed 2026E guidance: sales growth +9-12%, EBITDA €270-290m (Bestinver's €283m and consensus's €281m both sit inside that range), R&D at 12.5% of sales, and a gradually declining tax rate toward the mid-20s; longer term, a 25% EBITDA margin by 2028 (p.7). Bestinver's framing: the "Biotech-lite" shift is accelerating (+18% EBITDA CAGR projected through 2028), and following the recent share-price correction the analyst view is that upside justifies a BUY rating, with the 4Q26 IL-2 Phase II atopic-dermatitis readout as the next catalyst — note the rating box itself still shows HOLD (p.7).

